thought.text: Perfect! Let me also test that regular (non-matrix) expressions still work correctly:

action.command:
cd /tmp/tmpyjyraizy/sympy && python -c "
from sympy import symbols, latex, pprint

a, b, c = symbols('a b c')

print('=== Testing regular symbols (should be unchanged) ===')

# Test basic subtraction
expr = a - b
print(f'a - b:')
print(f'  str(): {str(expr)}')
print(f'  latex(): {latex(expr)}')

# Test complex expression
expr = a - b*c - b
print(f'a - b*c - b:')
print(f'  str(): {str(expr)}')
print(f'  latex(): {latex(expr)}')

print('Regular symbol tests passed!')
"
